		<p class="style57">&nbsp;</p>
		<p class="style57"><span class="style84">This series of images illustrates some 
			of the process involved in building a traditional piece of 
			furniture.</p>
			<p class="style57">Ian Laval makes extensive use of sawn veneers, 
			cut from the same local trees growing within reach of his workshop.</p>
			<p class="style57">These veneers are sawn -- generally one-eighth of 
			an inch thick -- from fresh, green timber. They are found in 
			crotches, burrs and a variety of interesting places in the tree 
			revealed in processing. They are then generally laid in book-matched 
			pairs or quarters to embellish the furniture.</span></span></p>
